## Database Schema — `backend/prisma/schema.prisma`

> **CRITICAL**: `datasource db` has NO `url =` field. Connection is injected via `PrismaMariaDb` adapter in `src/config/prisma.ts`. This is the Prisma v7 driver-adapter pattern.

### Enums
```
Role:          CITIZEN | NGO_ADMIN | VOLUNTEER | SUPER_ADMIN
RequestStatus: PENDING | UNDER_REVIEW | APPROVED | REJECTED | IN_PROGRESS | COMPLETED | CANCELLED
```

### Models (16 total)

| Model | Key Fields | Key Relations |
|---|---|---|
| `User` | id (uuid), email (unique), passwordHash, role, firstName, lastName, phone?, isActive, createdAt | → requests[], ngoProfile?, volunteerProfile?, notifications[], comments[], resourceDonations[], moneyDonations[] |
| `NGO` | id, userId (unique→User CASCADE), name, registrationNo (unique), description?, address, city, state, isVerified (default false) | → requests[], resources[], volunteers[], joinRequests[], VolunteerInterests[], resourceAllocations[], resourceDonations[], moneyDonations[], account?, expenses[] |
| `Volunteer` | id, userId (unique→User CASCADE), skills (Json?), bio?, isAvailable (default true) | → ngoMemberships[], assignments[], joinRequests[], interests[] |
| `Request` | id, citizenId, ngoId?, title, description (Text), category, status (enum), urgencyLevel (Int default 1), address/city/state, rejectionReason?, reviewedAt? | → assignments[], VolunteerInterests[], ResourceAllocations[], statusLogs[], comments[] |
| `Resource` | id, ngoId, name, type, quantity (Float), unit?, description? | → allocations[] |
| `VolunteerAssignment` | id, requestId, volunteerId, ngoId, assignedBy, status (default "ASSIGNED"), notes? | @@unique([requestId, volunteerId]) |
| `NGOVolunteer` | id, ngoId, volunteerId, joinedAt, isActive (default true) | @@unique([ngoId, volunteerId]) — roster join table |
| `VolunteerJoinRequest` | id, volunteerId, ngoId, message?, status (default "PENDING"), respondedAt? | @@unique([volunteerId, ngoId]) |
